eu.cqse.check.framework.core.phase

Interface ITokenElementContext

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ICheckContext

    public interface ITokenElementContext
    Context interface for accessing different views of a token element.

      Calculates the pre-processed tokens (no global include resolution).

    • Method Detail

      • getLanguage

        ELanguage getLanguage()
        Returns the language of the analyzed token element.

      • getUniformPath

        java.lang.String getUniformPath()
        Returns the uniform path of the analyzed token element.

      • getTokens

        java.util.List<IToken> getTokens(ECodeViewOption view)
                          throws CheckException
        Returns the tokens in the given view. This method can be used, if the executing check requests the ECheckParameter.ABSTRACT_SYNTAX_TREE parameter.
        Throws:
        CheckException

      • getTextContent

        java.lang.String getTextContent(ECodeViewOption.ETextViewOption view)
                         throws CheckException
        Returns the text content in the given view. For most checks the preferred form of content will be ECodeViewOption.ETextViewOption.FILTERED_CONTENT, as usually no findings shall be generated for filtered code.
        Throws:
        CheckException

      • getRootEntity

        ShallowEntity getRootEntity(ECodeViewOption view)
                     throws CheckException
        Returns the synthetic root entity of the abstract syntax tree based on the given view.

        This method can be used, if the executing check requests the ECheckParameter.ABSTRACT_SYNTAX_TREE parameter.

        Throws:
        CheckException

      • getAbstractSyntaxTree

        java.util.List<ShallowEntity> getAbstractSyntaxTree(ECodeViewOption view)
                                             throws CheckException
        Returns the abstract syntax tree of the analyzed token element as list of shallow entities based on the given view.

        This method can be used, if the executing check requests the ECheckParameter.ABSTRACT_SYNTAX_TREE parameter.

        Throws:
        CheckException

      • getLogger

        ILogger getLogger()
        Returns a logger, which may be used to indicate problems in situations where the check may continue. In more severe cases, a CheckException should be thrown instead.

      • getTypeResolution

        ITypeResolution getTypeResolution(ECodeViewOption view)
                           throws CheckException
        Returns a type resolution, which contains information about known variables and their types. This method can be used, if the executing check request the ECheckParameter.TYPE_RESOLUTION parameter. Based on the given ECodeViewOption.
        Throws:
        CheckException

      • calculateLocalPreprocessedTokens

        default java.util.List<IToken> calculateLocalPreprocessedTokens(java.util.List<IToken> tokens)
        Calculates the pre-processed tokens (no global include resolution).

      • getClangTranslationUnitWrapper

        ClangTranslationUnitWrapper getClangTranslationUnitWrapper()
        Returns a ClangTranslationUnitWrapper containing the initialized JNI interface to Clang for the current file. To access this, specify the ECheckParameter.CLANG option in the custom check.
